00:54.654 --> 00:59.489
<i>In the middle of Huntington,</i>
<i>West Virginia, there is a river.</i>

01:03.897 --> 01:06.991
<i>Next to this river, there is a steel mill.</i>

01:11.738 --> 01:14.866
<i>And next to the steel mill,</i>
<i>there is a school.</i>

01:20.246 --> 01:23.511
<i>In the middle of this school,</i>
<i>there is a fountain.</i>

01:25.919 --> 01:31.414
<i>Each year, on the exact same day,</i>
<i>at the exact same hour...</i>

01:31.591 --> 01:34.424
<i>...the water to this fountain is turned off.</i>

01:35.762 --> 01:39.027
<i>And in this moment, once every year...</i>

01:40.133 --> 01:44.194
<i>...throughout the town,</i>
<i>throughout the school...</i>

01:45.405 --> 01:47.771
<i>...time stands still.</i>

02:04.958 --> 02:07.984
Chris Griffen with a reception.
That is a first down.

02:08.161 --> 02:13.224
<i>But Marshall is all out of time-outs,</i>
<i>and the clock is now ticking.</i>

02:13.399 --> 02:16.562
<i>If they wanna get another play off,</i>
<i>the Herd had better hurry.</i>

02:17.570 --> 02:20.368
Call it in, Red! Call it in!

02:23.510 --> 02:27.810
-Griffen! Okay, Chris Griffen! Hustle up!
-l'm good, l'm good.

02:27.981 --> 02:29.710
The Herd looks a little disorganized.

02:29.883 --> 02:34.081
They're looking for a play from the sideline,
and they are almost out of time.

02:34.254 --> 02:37.382
<i>We are talking about seconds.</i>
<i>Marshall needs to get down and over--</i>

02:37.557 --> 02:39.548
-77-Victory. Go! Go, go, go!
-Yes, sir.

02:39.726 --> 02:41.557
77-Victory. You're out.

02:42.362 --> 02:46.423
V, 77! V, 77!

02:52.305 --> 02:53.932
Come on! Snap the ball!

02:54.807 --> 02:56.297
Set!

02:57.010 --> 03:01.003
Snap it! Snap it! Snap it!

03:01.915 --> 03:03.382
Come on!

03:04.250 --> 03:05.547
Hut!

03:14.527 --> 03:17.223
Strong side! He's open!

03:17.397 --> 03:19.763
He's open! Throw!

03:34.047 --> 03:36.777
<i>And that'll be it for the Herd.</i>

03:38.084 --> 03:40.314
That's right, the clock has hit all zeroes...

03:40.486 --> 03:43.546
<i>...and the Carolina faithful</i>
<i>are already on their feet.</i>

03:43.723 --> 03:44.951
<i>So there you have it.</i>

03:45.124 --> 03:46.887
<i>-It's all over, folks.</i>
-Good game, Red.

03:47.060 --> 03:51.554
<i>Marshall loses a tough one,</i>
<i>1 7- 1 4 to the East Carolina Pirates.</i>

03:51.731 --> 03:53.562
Red's got his work cut out for him.

03:53.733 --> 03:57.965
Well, there goes my weekend.
Red'll be in the film room till Monday.

03:58.137 --> 03:59.434
He'd better.

03:59.606 --> 04:02.404
Your husband hasn't figured out
how to beat the 3-4 all year.

04:02.575 --> 04:04.907
<i>Co-captain Nate Ruffin</i>
<i>and cornerback Tom Bogdan...</i>

04:05.078 --> 04:08.639
<i>...are two of four starters who were</i>
<i>left back in Huntington due to injuries.</i>

04:08.815 --> 04:12.683
Surprised to see you. Figured the chairman
of the school board would be at the game.

04:12.852 --> 04:15.047
This place won't run itself,
you know that.

04:15.221 --> 04:17.951
-Furnace ready for the tap?
-Yeah.

04:20.793 --> 04:23.489
<i>The next week is a must-win.</i>

04:23.663 --> 04:25.460
They're all must-wins, Gene.

04:25.632 --> 04:29.728
<i>No word yet on whether any or all of the</i>
<i>injured players will be available next--</i>

04:34.641 --> 04:37.804
Hey, Sandy, can l get
some more foil in here?

04:38.678 --> 04:42.944
<i>The score, 1 7- 1 4, East Carolina Pirates.</i>
<i>Quarterback Teddy Shoebridge....</i>

04:43.116 --> 04:44.583
l got it!

04:49.322 --> 04:53.315
Hey, where's the flag?
Where's the flag? Flag on--

04:53.493 --> 04:57.020
Fifty-five! Blocking in the--

04:57.196 --> 05:00.097
--if that confusion on the Marshall sideline
at the end of the game...

05:00.266 --> 05:04.202
...won't make that target on
Coach Tolley's back a little bit bigger.

05:04.370 --> 05:08.238
l'm not gonna ask you guys again.
Dinner's ready.

05:09.809 --> 05:11.640
That means you too, Keith.

05:11.811 --> 05:14.609
Please, just a few more seconds?
Dad's not off yet.

05:14.781 --> 05:17.944
He'll still be droning on about that game
when he gets home tonight.

05:18.117 --> 05:20.176
Get out from under there,
Keith Morehouse.

05:20.353 --> 05:24.881
l'm Gene Morehouse saying
good night, and go Herd!

05:25.158 --> 05:26.455
Fellas...

05:28.027 --> 05:30.393
...you gave a good effort out there today.

05:33.066 --> 05:35.193
But let me be clear about this:

05:35.601 --> 05:39.093
A good effort is not enough.

05:42.842 --> 05:44.707
Now, l'm proud of you.

05:46.479 --> 05:49.141
But l will not accept losing with you.

05:49.749 --> 05:52.081
Because there's only one thing
they judge us on.

05:52.251 --> 05:54.981
There's only one thing people remember.

05:56.022 --> 05:58.684
And it ain't how we play the game!

06:02.762 --> 06:04.354
Winning...

06:05.398 --> 06:07.025
...is everything.

06:11.003 --> 06:12.368
Plane leaves in an hour.

06:13.139 --> 06:15.198
We'll be home by 8.

06:15.375 --> 06:19.539
Plenty of time for y'all to do whatever
the hell y'all do on a Saturday night.

06:24.317 --> 06:27.286
Now, see, Bogdan, the reason we lost
is because we weren't there.

06:27.453 --> 06:31.321
Chocolate Thunder, White Lightning? We the
best defensive players in the conference.

06:31.491 --> 06:32.856
l'm Chocolate Thunder, right?

06:33.025 --> 06:35.721
Why you so scared to introduce me
to your girlfriend, then?

06:35.895 --> 06:37.920
Listen, stop being so
overconfident, Ruffin.

06:38.097 --> 06:41.863
All right, Rock, Paper, Scissors for tickets.
Let's go, right now.

06:44.103 --> 06:45.593
lt's okay. l'll get the popcorn.

06:45.772 --> 06:47.433
East Carolina?

06:47.607 --> 06:50.440
l mean, l can understand giving up
300 yards to Bowling Green.

06:50.610 --> 06:51.941
But East Carolina?

06:52.111 --> 06:55.137
Well, you can't do nothing
about injuries, you know?

06:55.715 --> 06:57.706
What happened? ls it broken?

06:57.884 --> 06:59.784
lt's dislocated.

06:59.952 --> 07:01.943
What's wrong with you, Tom?

07:02.922 --> 07:04.822
Come on, man. Gonna miss the previews.

07:04.991 --> 07:09.223
Nineteen carries, 1 08 yards, Paul,
your boy Chris played a hell of a game.

07:09.395 --> 07:11.863
l'd have taken the win any day.
lsn't that right, Don?

07:12.031 --> 07:14.056
What, now, we didn't win?

07:15.435 --> 07:18.404
You of all people, Don.
lf you're not gonna listen to the game...

07:18.571 --> 07:21.165
...you gotta know the result
so you can pretend you did.

07:21.340 --> 07:23.535
-Well, l'm doing my best, Paul.
-You hungry?

07:23.709 --> 07:25.643
No, thank you. l'm all set.

07:25.812 --> 07:28.645
Lloyd? Usual for me tonight,
just more of it. l'm starving.

07:28.815 --> 07:30.874
-You got it.
-Go ahead, excuse me.

07:31.050 --> 07:34.042
Well, the board has asked me
to run a few ideas through you...

07:34.220 --> 07:38.281
...about some potential improvements
to the university's physical plant.

07:48.634 --> 07:50.363
There's Chris!

07:53.773 --> 07:57.174
What took you so long to call?
Tell Joe he can't run it to the inside....

07:57.343 --> 07:59.971
Slow down, Reggie. Just listen.

08:00.146 --> 08:03.946
-l just need a favor, not your life story.
-What you need?

08:04.116 --> 08:08.985
l need you to go get us a case
of Falls City Beer. Falls City.

08:09.155 --> 08:12.750
-Go to the liquor store on Fourth. Yeah.
<i>-Fourth Street?</i>

08:12.925 --> 08:15.519
-Hey, are the guys with you?
-Yeah, Reggie.

08:15.695 --> 08:17.686
What is it, godd--?

08:18.364 --> 08:21.800
That's right, Reggie. You carry the two
and you divide by the sum....

08:21.968 --> 08:25.460
Yeah, math class is over.
Let's get on the plane. Come on.

08:28.241 --> 08:31.039
-l'll see you in a couple of hours, right?
-You know you are.

08:31.210 --> 08:33.337
-l'm gonna stay at my dad's house tonight.
-No.

08:33.513 --> 08:36.208
He's gonna wanna go over his
post-game breakdown.

08:36.649 --> 08:39.015
Sorry. We've been doing it
since l was a kid.

08:39.184 --> 08:41.346
You gonna tell him about California, right?

08:41.520 --> 08:45.355
Are you kidding? After a loss?
We want him in a good mood.

08:45.525 --> 08:47.117
Yeah.

08:47.393 --> 08:50.157
Don't worry. l will.

08:52.198 --> 08:54.166
Just not this weekend.

08:54.333 --> 08:56.460
Griffen! Let's go!

08:57.436 --> 08:59.427
l love you, Chris Griffen.

09:00.506 --> 09:02.497
Come on, Annie!

09:04.410 --> 09:06.844
-Race you back.
-Let's go! Hurry up!

09:07.013 --> 09:08.913
l'm coming!

09:14.520 --> 09:16.249
What's this concert you're missing?

09:16.422 --> 09:20.415
lt's just my granddaughter's piano recital.
Man, she sure is cute when she does that.

09:20.593 --> 09:23.391
That's the crap l missed
first time around with my boys.

09:23.563 --> 09:24.996
Now they got kids of their own.

09:25.164 --> 09:28.224
Anyway, got a long ride ahead of me.
Have a great flight.

09:28.401 --> 09:30.995
Hutch, tell you what,
l'll do the recruiting trip.

09:31.170 --> 09:35.607
You go home and see your granddaughter's
recital. l'm gonna do it. l'm doing it.

09:37.910 --> 09:40.743
-Thanks, Red. All right.
-l'll see you on Monday morning.

09:42.582 --> 09:44.447
Good man, Red.

09:45.318 --> 09:47.684
You can grab me a beer back home.

09:57.463 --> 10:00.591
<i>Because if he keeps on pulling</i>
<i>and no money comes out....</i>

10:00.766 --> 10:02.358
-Good evening.
<i>-Doris.</i>

10:02.535 --> 10:05.436
lt's Red Dawson, calling from Greenville.

10:06.472 --> 10:09.373
Could l trouble you to look and see
if Carole's home next door?

10:12.178 --> 10:13.611
Sure doesn't look like it, Red.

10:13.779 --> 10:16.646
Could you do me a big favor
and leave her a message for me?

10:16.816 --> 10:20.183
Tell her that l gotta drive to Virginia
tonight on a recruiting trip...

10:20.353 --> 10:22.378
<i>...and I'm not gonna be home</i>
<i>till tomorrow.</i>

10:22.555 --> 10:24.716
-Got it.
<i>-All right, you have a good night, now.</i>

10:24.890 --> 10:27.415
-All right, bye.
<i>-Night, Red.</i>

10:45.011 --> 10:48.572
-You thinking about that girlfriend of yours?
-Yeah, coach.

10:50.016 --> 10:51.677
Nice job, son.

10:53.019 --> 10:54.816
Hey, that was a big hit today. Big hit.

10:54.987 --> 10:57.080
l would've caught that pass
if l had my cross.

10:57.256 --> 10:58.484
What'd you do with it?

10:58.658 --> 11:02.116
You would've caught it if you had good
hands. Ain't that right, Shoebridge?

11:02.294 --> 11:07.163
Hey, Gene, this is gonna sound a little
weird, but l need you to do me a favor.

11:07.333 --> 11:10.530
Want you to scratch my back.
That target on there is starting to itch.

11:10.703 --> 11:13.035
You can't believe everything
you hear on the radio.

11:13.205 --> 11:15.105
Oh, yeah, l can.

11:18.577 --> 11:23.344
All right, boys, let's sit up straight.
Tighten those ties, fix those collars.

11:23.516 --> 11:25.450
-We are?
-Marshall!

11:26.252 --> 11:27.719
Almost home.

11:30.222 --> 11:32.452
<i>This is Captain Dettro speaking.</i>

11:32.625 --> 11:35.287
<i>Looks like we made good time</i>
<i>in spite of the weather...</i>

11:35.461 --> 11:40.262
<i>...so if everyone could return to their</i>
<i>seats now, we'll be landing shortly.</i>

12:09.729 --> 12:11.526
Fill her up for you?

12:11.764 --> 12:13.129
Yes, sir.

12:18.871 --> 12:20.600
These peanuts look good.

12:22.274 --> 12:24.208
l'll get a bunch of them too.

12:24.376 --> 12:27.504
Sure. They're just 50 cents.
Help yourself.

12:27.680 --> 12:30.649
Regular's on the left,
Cajun's on the right.

12:30.816 --> 12:33.080
<i>Incredibly, there has been</i>
<i>another plane crash....</i>

12:33.252 --> 12:34.981
How spicy are these Cajun...?

12:35.154 --> 12:38.385
<i>--in moderate rain and fog</i>
<i>in West Virginia.</i>

12:38.557 --> 12:40.286
What did he just say?

12:40.459 --> 12:42.324
-Wait. Turn that up.
-No, what happened--

12:42.495 --> 12:43.723
What did that say?

12:43.896 --> 12:47.457
<i>Early reports do not indicate</i>
<i>the condition of those aboard.</i>

12:54.140 --> 12:55.437
Excuse me, everybody....

12:55.608 --> 12:57.007
<i>Annette said you look funny</i>
<i>when you're getting dressed.</i>

13:02.615 --> 13:04.708
Bye, Carole.
Say hello to your husband for me.

13:04.884 --> 13:07.717
-This is Lloyd.
-See you, Lloyd!

13:15.594 --> 13:17.152
What's happened?

13:29.742 --> 13:31.437
Hey!

13:34.180 --> 13:36.876
-Hey, you going to the airport?
-Yeah, get in.

13:37.049 --> 13:40.917
All right. l'm getting in. Hold on.
All right, good.

13:59.905 --> 14:02.135
-Hey, did they say anything?
-Hey, come on!

14:02.308 --> 14:05.766
No one's going in there.
l can't let you up there.

14:05.945 --> 14:07.970
-Get that truck up the hill!
-Come on!

14:08.147 --> 14:09.546
Hey, Randy!

14:11.517 --> 14:13.109
Come on, keep going, come on.

14:17.756 --> 14:19.451
Hey, watch the hose!

14:31.337 --> 14:34.568
Got the president of the university here!

14:36.442 --> 14:38.433
Oh, my God in heaven.

14:39.511 --> 14:41.536
Oh, my God.

14:46.952 --> 14:48.613
Come on.

14:50.155 --> 14:51.850
Let's go.

14:53.158 --> 14:56.184
-Hey, get behind the ropes!
-Just tell us the name of the airline!

14:56.362 --> 14:59.729
-lf l knew anything, l'd tell you!
-Just look at the front of the plane!

14:59.899 --> 15:02.925
Son, there is no
front of the plane anymore.

15:06.538 --> 15:07.903
Bring another hose down here!

15:08.073 --> 15:10.837
No, stay back. Stay up there! No!

15:11.010 --> 15:14.002
-Let's go!
-Nate! Nate Ruffin!

15:14.947 --> 15:18.576
This our boys' plane?
This our boys' plane?!

16:48.774 --> 16:50.674
lt's so terrible.

17:39.024 --> 17:40.252
You didn't get my message?

18:00.712 --> 18:04.170
<i>Marshall University in West Virginia</i>
<i>is in a state of shock today...</i>

18:04.349 --> 18:08.877
<i>...following the terrible tragedy of last</i>
<i>Saturday night's crash of a chartered airline.</i>

18:09.054 --> 18:11.181
<i>Seventy-five people died in the wreckage.</i>

18:11.356 --> 18:13.085
<i>The football team, the coaches...</i>

18:13.258 --> 18:16.421
<i>...and some prominent residents</i>
<i>traveling with the team....</i>

18:47.526 --> 18:49.687
<i>These were beautiful young men...</i>

18:49.862 --> 18:55.061
<i>...and it's just a tragedy</i>
<i>that is beyond all comprehension.</i>

19:24.429 --> 19:28.866
<i>No one of us will ever</i>
<i>enter this stadium...</i>

19:29.034 --> 19:32.060
<i>...without thoughts of them.</i>

19:32.971 --> 19:39.206
<i>And so, our Lord, grant them</i>
<i>eternal rest and peace...</i>

19:39.478 --> 19:42.641
<i>...which enables them</i>
<i>at this very moment...</i>

19:42.814 --> 19:48.411
<i>...to look upon us here</i>
<i>and smile and be with us.</i>

19:48.587 --> 19:53.320
<i>This is our faith, this is our hope.</i>

19:54.459 --> 19:56.086
<i>Amen.</i>

20:27.025 --> 20:29.459
<i>Those were not welcome days.</i>

20:30.862 --> 20:32.762
<i>We buried sons...</i>

20:32.965 --> 20:34.626
<i>...brothers...</i>

20:34.800 --> 20:36.267
<i>...mothers...</i>

20:36.435 --> 20:38.528
<i>...fathers...</i>

20:39.304 --> 20:40.794
<i>...fiancés.</i>

20:48.614 --> 20:52.675
<i>Clocks ticked, but time did not pass.</i>

21:00.292 --> 21:03.523
<i>The sun rose and the sun set.</i>

21:05.197 --> 21:07.665
<i>But the shadows remained.</i>

21:11.803 --> 21:13.532
<i>When once there was sound...</i>

21:15.140 --> 21:17.608
<i>...now there was silence.</i>

21:28.320 --> 21:30.220
<i>What once was whole...</i>

21:31.223 --> 21:33.623
<i>...now is shattered.</i>

22:02.187 --> 22:04.849
Have you mentioned this
to any of the other board members?

22:05.023 --> 22:09.016
A few. Most of them
would prefer not to think about it.

22:09.194 --> 22:12.254
l can understand that sentiment.

22:12.431 --> 22:16.128
lt doesn't make sense to rush
right back into it, you know?

22:16.301 --> 22:19.634
Our coaching staff, gone.
Our athletic department, gone.

22:19.805 --> 22:22.968
So many of our boosters, gone.

22:23.141 --> 22:25.666
We'd have to start
all over again from scratch.

22:25.844 --> 22:30.042
My God, we don't have the resources
or the manpower right now.

22:30.215 --> 22:33.184
l know all the reasons
to suspend the program, Paul.

22:33.352 --> 22:35.479
l'm just surprised to hear it
coming from you.

22:35.654 --> 22:37.815
This town just didn't lose
a football team, Don.

22:37.989 --> 22:41.618
We lost doctors, lawyers,
city councilmen.

22:41.793 --> 22:44.284
We lost fathers, sons, husbands.

22:44.463 --> 22:49.457
How many kids lost a parent?
How many kids lost both parents?

22:49.634 --> 22:53.297
-Twenty-eight.
-Wouldn't be a game anymore, Don.

22:54.072 --> 22:56.768
Be a weekly reminder of what we've lost.

22:57.943 --> 23:02.209
And l just don't see how that would
do anyone in this town any good.

23:03.548 --> 23:06.711
Somebody's going to
have to tell them, Paul.

23:09.054 --> 23:12.114
All your scholarships will still be honored.

23:12.824 --> 23:17.557
Boys, it's very important that
we take a collective breath, as a town...

23:17.729 --> 23:20.289
...and figure out the
proper course of action.

23:20.465 --> 23:23.662
And you think the proper course of action
is ending the program?

23:23.835 --> 23:28.238
l didn't say we were going to end the
program, l said we are going to suspend it.

23:28.807 --> 23:33.835
Look, under the best of circumstances,
it takes years to build a team...

23:34.679 --> 23:37.614
...and, well, these are not
the best of circumstances.

23:37.783 --> 23:40.616
The NCAA will not let freshmen play...

23:40.786 --> 23:44.244
...and they are the only players
we have besides you.

23:45.257 --> 23:49.284
When we do bring the program back, we
want to make sure we're able to do it right.

23:49.461 --> 23:52.294
lf. That's what you mean, right?

23:52.464 --> 23:54.329
lf they bring the program back?

23:58.637 --> 24:01.299
This ain't right, Dr. Dedmon.
lt ain't fair!

24:01.473 --> 24:04.101
l understand your position, son.

24:04.376 --> 24:08.312
l will personally pass on your concerns to
the board before they make their decision.

24:08.480 --> 24:10.345
Why can't l pass on
my concerns myself?

24:11.650 --> 24:15.245
Well, unfortunately, board of governors'
meetings are and always have been...

24:15.420 --> 24:16.648
...closed-door.

24:20.859 --> 24:22.190
Come on!

24:22.360 --> 24:24.225
Everybody up! Let's go. Come on.

24:24.396 --> 24:26.489
Reggie, put down the stick. Come on.

24:26.665 --> 24:28.326
l need y'all to listen.

24:29.267 --> 24:33.397
Now, as of 1 5 minutes ago,
we ain't got football no more.

24:35.273 --> 24:38.436
lf you gonna be Marshall,
you gonna be Marshall right now.

24:39.411 --> 24:41.208
Earn your stripes.

24:44.316 --> 24:47.251
Now, l want the two of you
to go with Randy...

24:47.419 --> 24:50.547
...and get every cheerleader and every girl
you can possibly find...

24:50.722 --> 24:54.419
...and get them here at 5:00. The two
of y'all, l need you to go with George...

24:54.593 --> 24:58.085
...and find every cat in them frat houses
and get them here at 5:00.

24:58.263 --> 24:59.924
Go, now, go!

25:00.098 --> 25:01.656
l need you on this one, Reggie.

25:02.467 --> 25:04.332
l need you, man.

25:04.970 --> 25:07.734
Find every person y'all met
in freshman orientation...

25:07.906 --> 25:10.374
...and l need them here at 5:00.

25:10.542 --> 25:13.807
All right? Come on! Now! Come on!

25:14.246 --> 25:16.009
-Five o'clock!
-Nate.

25:16.181 --> 25:18.240
-Yeah.
-Come here a sec.

25:19.551 --> 25:22.611
Hey, l heard that some
of the guys are wavering.

25:23.755 --> 25:26.121
-Wavering?
-Yeah, they're just kind of....

25:26.291 --> 25:30.660
No, no, no. What you mean? What you
talking about? Who's wavering, Tom?

25:31.563 --> 25:35.192
They don't feel it's the right thing to do
right now, step out on that field.

25:35.367 --> 25:37.961
lt's the only thing to do, Tom.

25:38.136 --> 25:40.696
This about our teammates, man.

25:41.172 --> 25:43.970
Now, l need to know
who you talking about.

25:46.511 --> 25:48.240
No one, man.

25:49.781 --> 25:51.681
Five o'clock. All right?

25:53.051 --> 25:55.076
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

25:55.253 --> 25:57.881
-You all right?
-Forget it.

25:58.056 --> 26:00.889
l was just having some thoughts.
l'm ready, man. Let's go.

26:02.127 --> 26:04.425
-We gonna get this team back, man.
-Yeah.

26:08.166 --> 26:11.158
Okay, l think we all know
why we're here today.

26:11.336 --> 26:13.361
What l'd like to do first....

26:19.110 --> 26:23.809
Excuse me, young man.
Excuse me, this is a private meeting.

26:24.316 --> 26:28.810
l don't mean to interrupt, sir, but l think
there's something y'all need to hear.

26:29.254 --> 26:33.850
lf you have anything to say, we'll set up
a time for you to come by my office.

26:34.859 --> 26:38.590
Oh, no, sir. l ain't got nothing to say.

26:42.634 --> 26:44.534
But they do.

