<i>We are Marshall!</i>

29:16.387 --> 29:17.786
Hey, Mr. Boone.

29:19.190 --> 29:21.351
Annie, honey, come here.

29:23.194 --> 29:25.389
You don't have to come back
to work right away.

29:25.563 --> 29:28.828
Take some time for yourself.
The job will be waiting when you get back.

29:29.000 --> 29:31.764
One thing l don't need
is more time for myself.

29:32.771 --> 29:35.262
l just want things to get back to normal.

29:40.812 --> 29:42.780
Hi, Mr. Griffen.

29:43.648 --> 29:47.209
lt's good to see you.
Glad you're not giving up the booth.

29:47.385 --> 29:51.685
l've been coming here every day
for 30 years. No reason to stop now.

30:09.507 --> 30:11.975
l think you should have this back.

30:14.679 --> 30:16.806
Chris gave it to you.

30:18.149 --> 30:20.174
Yeah, he did.

30:21.619 --> 30:24.247
But you gave it to your wife first.

30:25.657 --> 30:28.626
And then you passed it down to him...

30:28.960 --> 30:31.724
...so l'm passing it back up to you.

30:33.531 --> 30:36.091
lt should stay in your family.

30:38.503 --> 30:40.471
What family?

30:43.641 --> 30:45.108
Annie...

30:46.377 --> 30:48.140
...you keep it.

30:48.546 --> 30:52.846
Wear it. And every morning
you put it on, you think of him.

31:27.886 --> 31:30.878
-Don.
-Red.

31:33.358 --> 31:34.723
What are you working on there?

31:34.893 --> 31:39.057
Well, l been promising Carole
a new shed for a while now, so....

31:39.230 --> 31:41.664
No time like the present, l guess.

31:43.768 --> 31:45.565
Red, l've got an offer for you.

31:51.075 --> 31:53.305
l was afraid you might.

32:02.587 --> 32:05.420
<i>Mrs. Dawson, if it had been me...</i>

32:05.590 --> 32:09.117
...l don't even know how l'd make it out
of bed in the morning.

32:11.562 --> 32:14.190
Let him build a hundred sheds.

32:18.703 --> 32:21.604
<i>Hello, this is President Donald Dedmon.</i>

32:22.774 --> 32:27.370
We've decided to go ahead
with our football program next season...

32:27.545 --> 32:32.141
...and your name was the first
on a list of potential candidates...

32:32.317 --> 32:36.276
...for the head coaching position.

32:37.989 --> 32:41.186
Well, no, l completely
understand. l just....

32:41.359 --> 32:44.123
You were the first one
on my list, so l....

32:49.434 --> 32:53.564
No. No, we decided
to bring the program back.

32:54.138 --> 32:57.164
Yes, it wasn't an easy decision.

32:57.342 --> 33:00.971
No, that's totally understandable. l....

33:04.515 --> 33:07.348
Well, thank you very much for...

33:07.518 --> 33:11.010
...well, taking the time
to at least talk with me about it.

33:14.625 --> 33:19.255
As l've been told,
you had a great career at Marshall and....

33:25.570 --> 33:27.162
Yes, thank you.

33:29.774 --> 33:31.833
No, l understand.

33:32.643 --> 33:34.338
No, l....

33:34.545 --> 33:36.536
Please, it's....

33:41.886 --> 33:43.547
Hey, honey?

33:44.622 --> 33:46.214
You ever been to Huntington before?

33:46.391 --> 33:49.554
Mouth closed, Peter. Thank you.

33:49.727 --> 33:51.217
West Virginia?

33:51.396 --> 33:52.795
No.

33:53.164 --> 33:54.631
Why?

33:55.299 --> 33:57.028
Just curious.

33:57.435 --> 34:00.199
-Hey, Peter.
-Yeah?

34:04.542 --> 34:07.010
Been quieter than l would've
guessed this morning.

34:07.578 --> 34:10.012
Ernie Salvatore called from the <i>Herald.</i>

34:10.181 --> 34:12.741
Says he wants to talk
if you have a moment.

34:12.917 --> 34:14.908
Oh, and there was another call.

34:15.085 --> 34:19.250
A Jack Lengyel called
from the College of Wooster.

34:19.424 --> 34:23.793
Says he may be interested
in the open coaching job.

34:24.228 --> 34:25.820
Wooster.

34:25.996 --> 34:27.987
Where in the world is Wooster?

34:28.266 --> 34:30.893
Does it really matter?

34:36.808 --> 34:39.333
Okay, now, let's show Dr. Dedmon
how it's done here.

34:39.510 --> 34:43.969
Run hard, knees high. Play till
the whistle blows. 1 7-Razor, on three.

34:44.148 --> 34:47.447
On three, 1 7-Razor.
Hut, hut, hut. Go, go, go!

34:47.618 --> 34:51.987
There he goes. There he goes.
Oh, first down!

34:53.056 --> 34:54.956
-You see that? Oh, yeah.
-ls he all right?

34:55.126 --> 34:58.186
Hey, 32, are you all right?
All right, go kill your brother.

34:58.362 --> 35:01.388
Now, you see that? Point is,
that tree wouldn't have been there...

35:01.566 --> 35:03.534
...if you had a fullback blocking for him.

35:03.701 --> 35:06.465
And that is why l'm a fan
of the Power l Formation.

35:06.637 --> 35:12.371
Well, l'm sorry, l'm afraid l haven't the
faintest idea what a Power l Formation is.

35:12.543 --> 35:14.238
Oh, you don't?
Oh, thank you, dear.

35:14.412 --> 35:16.403
-You're welcome.
-Power l Formation...

35:16.581 --> 35:20.847
...is just your basic offensive scheme.
Put the fullback in front of the tailback.

35:21.018 --> 35:24.181
Now, frankly, Jack, l don't care to know.

35:24.522 --> 35:30.154
Actually, l'm confident that l'm better off
not knowing what one is, l think.

35:30.862 --> 35:36.129
Well, Dr. Dedmon, on that,
we will have to agree to disagree.

35:36.501 --> 35:37.900
Thank you.

35:40.371 --> 35:44.068
Jack, there is one thing l need to know...

35:44.342 --> 35:46.708
...and please excuse me if l seem blunt.

35:47.879 --> 35:52.441
You are the first person l've interviewed
who is not an alumnus.

35:52.984 --> 35:56.112
And, well, since you called us...

35:56.521 --> 36:00.150
...l have to ask what your angle is, Jack.

36:01.125 --> 36:05.653
You've got a great setup here.
You have no ties to Marshall.

36:06.063 --> 36:08.531
Why do you want this job?

36:08.699 --> 36:11.293
Who in their right mind
would volunteer for something...?

36:11.469 --> 36:14.529
Son, don't put that in your mouth.
No, put it down. That's right.

36:14.705 --> 36:18.163
-lt's not an outrageous question, l think.
-What's he gonna do?

36:18.342 --> 36:21.277
He's gonna put it in his pants?
l bet he puts it in his pants.

36:21.445 --> 36:25.006
-Son, don't put that in your pant-- Sandy!
-l got it. Peter.

36:25.183 --> 36:26.548
l'm sorry, excuse me.

36:26.717 --> 36:31.950
Well, l was just wondering if you had
given this any thought at all...

36:32.123 --> 36:34.990
...before you asked me to drive 200 miles
out here to see you.

36:36.360 --> 36:38.055
A little bit, yeah.

36:38.529 --> 36:40.121
Little bit.

36:45.703 --> 36:47.295
Well, all right, then.

36:47.872 --> 36:50.670
l have a long ride home...

36:50.841 --> 36:53.503
...and l should be getting on with it.

36:53.678 --> 36:56.374
You thank your wife for the lovely dinner.

36:56.547 --> 36:58.708
-Are you sure? Okay.
-Yes, thank--

36:58.883 --> 37:00.350
Thank you.

37:03.554 --> 37:05.215
Say, Don?

37:08.025 --> 37:10.585
You wanna know why
l picked up the phone? ls that it?

37:10.761 --> 37:12.991
Frankly, l do.

37:13.698 --> 37:17.725
-lt's not gonna be complicated.
-Jack, l've had four months of complicated.

37:17.902 --> 37:19.494
l just need honest.

37:33.084 --> 37:37.748
When l heard about
what had happened, your situation...

37:39.290 --> 37:43.750
...the only thing l could think about
was the four of them.

37:46.597 --> 37:49.498
l thought about how much
they mean to me...

37:51.135 --> 37:53.603
...and about how bad it would hurt if....

37:55.506 --> 37:57.599
Well, if l was to lose them.

38:00.911 --> 38:04.278
Then l thought about a team...

38:06.417 --> 38:08.146
...and a school...

38:09.420 --> 38:11.411
...and a town...

38:12.757 --> 38:14.486
...that's gotta be hurting real bad.

38:17.295 --> 38:19.195
And l thought, hell...

38:19.997 --> 38:21.828
...maybe l can help.

38:27.938 --> 38:29.906
So l called you.

38:34.512 --> 38:35.945
Yeah.

38:37.948 --> 38:41.406
l guess that's the only real ''why'' l got.
Right there.

38:42.320 --> 38:44.049
Touchdown.

38:49.727 --> 38:51.160
<i>Ladies and gentlemen...</i>

38:51.329 --> 38:55.857
...please welcome the new head coach
of our Thundering Herd...

38:56.033 --> 38:57.728
...Jack Lengyel.

39:05.810 --> 39:07.402
Hi there.

39:16.821 --> 39:18.516
Thank you.

39:22.159 --> 39:28.655
l am honored to be the new head
football coach here at Marshall University.

39:29.767 --> 39:35.364
Also would like to say a big thank you
from myself, my wife and our three kids.

39:35.539 --> 39:39.305
We drove in from Wooster last night.
Arrived at our new home here.

39:39.477 --> 39:42.844
Electricity worked,
the water pressure was high.

39:43.013 --> 39:46.710
There was a six-pack of beer in the fridge
and a pound cake on the counter.

39:47.418 --> 39:50.478
Four for four.
We appreciate the hospitality, we really do.

39:53.457 --> 39:55.049
Any questions?

39:56.761 --> 39:57.989
-Coach?
-Yes, sir.

39:58.162 --> 40:00.221
Ernie Salvatore, <i>Herald-Dispatch.</i>

40:00.398 --> 40:03.595
Now, realistically, coach,
what are your expectations for the season?

40:05.136 --> 40:07.536
Well, l can tell you this...

40:08.272 --> 40:10.740
...if it's a miracle you're looking for...

40:11.876 --> 40:15.539
...well, you should keep looking, because
you're gonna end up disappointed...

40:15.713 --> 40:17.704
...and l'm gonna end up out of a job.

40:17.915 --> 40:21.146
Follow-up, coach. Follow-up.
One quick follow-up, coach.

40:21.318 --> 40:24.082
What would you say to
the family members in the community...

40:24.255 --> 40:29.454
...who feel that putting the team back
on that field might be disrespectful?

40:36.300 --> 40:38.165
l am a football coach.

40:38.636 --> 40:42.367
That is what l do
and that's why l'm here.

40:44.208 --> 40:45.641
l guess that's it.

40:45.810 --> 40:47.835
l have no idea.
What kind of answer was that?

40:48.012 --> 40:49.138
How many clichés...?

40:49.480 --> 40:52.449
Are there any other questions?

40:52.817 --> 40:54.409
This guy won't make it.

40:56.821 --> 40:58.982
So this is my varsity team, huh?

41:00.124 --> 41:01.682
There was four of us...

41:04.128 --> 41:07.962
...but one of us ain't here,
so l guess it's just three.

41:08.499 --> 41:09.830
Okay.

41:11.035 --> 41:13.765
l'm Coach Jack Lengyel, guys.

41:14.071 --> 41:16.471
Normally, l'm bad with names,
so the good news is...

41:16.640 --> 41:19.507
...l may actually be able
to keep you fellas straight.

41:20.044 --> 41:21.944
Nate, is it?

41:22.112 --> 41:25.377
Okay, now, hold on
while l commit this to memory. Nate.

41:25.850 --> 41:27.841
As in Nate the Great.

41:28.018 --> 41:30.748
Date, late, escape. Wait. Nate.

41:30.921 --> 41:32.684
McDrake.

41:32.857 --> 41:37.191
l got it. Locked.
Kid l went to grade school with.

41:37.361 --> 41:40.853
See, that's a little word-association trick
l learned. Helps jog the recall.

41:41.031 --> 41:44.228
l read about it in <i>Redbook.</i>
And l tell you what, it really works, too.

41:45.469 --> 41:48.029
Well, we're in this together now, boys.

41:49.173 --> 41:51.971
l'm not going anywhere,
and that's a promise.

41:52.810 --> 41:54.072
Already got one name down.

41:55.212 --> 41:57.612
Soon as the wife gets things
settled at the house...

41:57.781 --> 42:01.217
...y'all are coming over for supper,
and l'll get the other two.

42:03.020 --> 42:05.181
We are Marshall.

42:07.992 --> 42:09.857
lt's a new day, men.

42:11.896 --> 42:14.729
l like those boys, Don. l do. l do.

42:14.899 --> 42:17.367
The thing is, l'm gonna need
55 more just like them.

42:17.535 --> 42:20.504
Oh, that l can't help you with, l'm afraid.

42:20.738 --> 42:22.831
Well, actually, you can, Don.

42:23.941 --> 42:28.537
You see, l need you to petition
the NCAA for me.

42:28.712 --> 42:33.342
Ask them to make an exception.
Allow us to play freshmen.

42:33.517 --> 42:36.577
Now, it's the only chance we have
to get any edge on recruiting...

42:36.754 --> 42:39.450
...much less put a full football team
on the field.

42:39.623 --> 42:41.853
l mean, we are way behind here.

42:42.026 --> 42:46.190
Well, you know the NCAA
better than l do, Jack.

42:46.363 --> 42:50.094
They're rigid as a board.
They don't make exceptions.

42:51.468 --> 42:52.935
Usually true.

42:53.771 --> 42:55.102
Yeah.

42:56.473 --> 43:01.410
Hey, you know, my son, he crapped
his pants yesterday. Now, he's 4.

43:01.579 --> 43:04.946
All right, now, my wife is out shopping,
so l had to clean him up.

43:05.783 --> 43:08.217
She got home. l told her what happened.
She says, ''l can't believe it.''

43:08.385 --> 43:11.149
l said, ''l can't believe it either.
The kid's 4 years old...

43:11.322 --> 43:13.586
...he shouldn't be doing that shit.''
Pun intended.

43:13.757 --> 43:16.555
You know what she says to me?
She says, ''Jack, no, not that.

43:17.161 --> 43:20.597
l can't believe you finally
changed a diaper.''

43:22.466 --> 43:24.491
What are you talking about?

43:25.302 --> 43:27.600
There's a first time for everything.

43:31.342 --> 43:32.741
Hey, l know you.

43:32.910 --> 43:35.208
ln the middle. Yes, l do.

43:35.379 --> 43:39.110
Ask me your name. Go ahead,
l won't even look. Ask me your name.

43:40.150 --> 43:43.347
-What's my name?
-Nate Ruffin.

43:43.520 --> 43:47.115
Team co-captain. Eleven interceptions
in only seven games last year.

43:49.927 --> 43:51.485
<i>Redbook.</i>

43:51.996 --> 43:53.486
Stuff really works.

43:53.664 --> 43:55.825
Hey, we can do this, doc.

44:02.873 --> 44:06.468
What are those, 1 -by-5s?

44:06.644 --> 44:07.872
One-by-sixes.

44:09.580 --> 44:12.413
They don't look that wide from down here.

44:15.619 --> 44:19.020
-Saw you guys play once.
-Did we win?

44:19.957 --> 44:21.982
lt was the Ashland game.

44:22.292 --> 44:23.691
Well, that'd be a no, then.

44:24.862 --> 44:27.990
Well, you guys looked pretty good
till the fourth quarter.

44:29.133 --> 44:31.397
Probably should've gone to the nickel.

44:33.370 --> 44:35.497
You know, you're probably right.

44:35.673 --> 44:38.198
You know, l appreciate you
coming out here to see me...

44:38.375 --> 44:42.971
...but they already came out here to ask me
back and l already told them that l'm not...

44:44.481 --> 44:47.575
-...coming back, so....
-Yeah, l heard. l heard about that.

44:49.319 --> 44:53.085
Just thought l could make you
a better offer.

44:53.557 --> 44:56.321
You know, they asked you
to be the head coach.

44:57.227 --> 44:59.161
l want you to be the assistant coach.

45:01.198 --> 45:03.257
l think that's a demotion, Jack.

45:03.434 --> 45:04.958
Well, maybe.

45:05.402 --> 45:06.869
Maybe not.

45:07.037 --> 45:11.235
l mean, it's the same duties,
practically, just less pay.

45:12.543 --> 45:15.706
Same hours. Less responsibility.

45:15.879 --> 45:18.006
Same team, less pressure.

45:19.383 --> 45:24.252
l tell you, Red, you know,
the cupboard is pretty bare.

45:24.421 --> 45:28.551
And l could use some recruiting help
from someone who knows the area.

45:35.432 --> 45:38.458
You know, Carole and l
moved here two years ago. lt was...

45:39.937 --> 45:41.905
...spring of '69.

45:44.208 --> 45:46.108
They had hired me as a receivers coach...

45:46.276 --> 45:50.076
...but when l got here, they told me
l was in charge of recruiting too, so....

45:50.981 --> 45:55.611
That first year l went out
and l got us 20 kids.

45:56.253 --> 46:00.917
Went to 20 homes.
Sat in 20 living rooms.

46:02.159 --> 46:05.890
And l promised 20 mothers
that l'd look after their sons.

46:07.898 --> 46:10.423
lt'd have been the class of '73.

46:14.638 --> 46:16.936
There's not one of them left.

46:20.944 --> 46:23.071
So let me ask you, Jack:

46:24.481 --> 46:28.975
How am l supposed to look a mother in the
eye and promise her anything ever again?

46:35.292 --> 46:37.317
l don't know, Red.

46:45.335 --> 46:48.600
l just don't think l could
take that field again, Jack.

47:00.617 --> 47:04.053
ls that the Ohio Valley Coal line?

47:04.221 --> 47:07.122
The same one that went off the tracks
near Akron last winter?

47:07.291 --> 47:10.317
Yep. That's the one.

47:11.195 --> 47:13.095
Back on track.

47:18.502 --> 47:22.029
Well, listen,
if you're able to figure it out...

47:22.206 --> 47:24.970
...door's always open.
lt was a pleasure meeting you, Red.

47:25.142 --> 47:27.110
Nice meeting you.

47:27.277 --> 47:31.145
l'll keep that defensive-nickel
package idea in mind...

47:31.315 --> 47:35.513
...for my fourth quarters in the future.
Maybe get a few more W's.

47:37.321 --> 47:38.913
One-by-six, huh?

47:39.089 --> 47:40.317
Yup.

47:40.490 --> 47:43.857
Same coverage, less boards.

47:48.065 --> 47:49.396
Hey, Tom.

47:52.069 --> 47:54.094
Guess we got us a coach, huh?

48:03.347 --> 48:04.871
Hey, look.

48:06.283 --> 48:10.686
When they first roomed us together
freshman year, l wasn't too sure about you.

48:11.855 --> 48:15.951
You know? But we stuck it out,
and now you're my best friend.

48:17.261 --> 48:19.627
l mean, remember freshman two-a-days?

48:19.796 --> 48:23.698
l'm puking my guts out and
l wanna quit football and you won't let me?

48:25.135 --> 48:27.729
Now, you never gave up on us
out there on the field...

48:27.905 --> 48:30.396
...and l'm not gonna give up on you now.

48:34.378 --> 48:36.039
Tom, man.

48:36.213 --> 48:41.947
lt's our team. Now, they left this to us.
lt's up to us! lt's on our shoulders, man.

48:43.487 --> 48:45.785
l need you with me, Tom.

48:45.956 --> 48:48.220
l should've been with them, Nate.

48:48.392 --> 48:52.590
-Look, Tom, l understand, and l feel--
-No, you don't! You don't, Nate! You don't.

48:54.898 --> 48:57.162
What you talking about?

48:59.369 --> 49:01.337
l overslept.

49:02.239 --> 49:05.265
That's why l wasn't on the plane, Nate.
l overslept.

49:05.943 --> 49:08.810
l wasn't hurt or sick.
And l should've been there.

49:08.979 --> 49:11.004
l should have been with them!

49:12.783 --> 49:16.844
l'm sorry. l just can't play football
right now. Okay? lt's not in me.

49:19.389 --> 49:22.586
l can't do it, you understand that, right?
Look at me.

49:25.362 --> 49:26.989
l'm sorry.

49:27.364 --> 49:29.025
Tom.

49:46.950 --> 49:49.316
Thought you might like some dessert.

49:50.787 --> 49:52.687
Thank you, Annie.

49:53.890 --> 49:55.551
l'm gonna get you some silverware.

50:57.821 --> 50:59.311
Yup.

51:00.290 --> 51:01.621
Game day.

51:07.898 --> 51:09.297
Yup.

51:18.442 --> 51:23.607
So l'll give you one year.

51:26.183 --> 51:29.584
Well, if that's all the time we've got,
we'd better get started.

51:42.532 --> 51:44.090
Coach Mickey Jackson.

51:46.736 --> 51:48.533
Coach McNally.

51:52.075 --> 51:53.599
Coach Riley.

51:56.379 --> 52:02.113
First line: NCAA, address--
l assume you have it, Luann.

52:02.285 --> 52:04.412
lt's somewhere in Kansas City.

52:04.588 --> 52:08.524
Salutation: To whom it may concern.

52:09.593 --> 52:12.790
As l am sure you are aware, we....

52:13.763 --> 52:16.231
l'm gonna take a road trip
southeast of here...

52:16.399 --> 52:19.926
...and go get this Shaw kid
down in Martinsville.

52:20.103 --> 52:22.094
l'm gonna take a shot at Gibbs.

52:22.272 --> 52:24.502
Go get us a quarterback, coach.

52:39.322 --> 52:42.291
-Jake. Red Dawson.
-Yes, sir?

52:50.333 --> 52:53.700
l know coaches from quite a few schools
have already come to talk...

52:53.870 --> 52:57.829
...about your son playing football for them.
l hope that he hasn't made his mind up.

52:58.008 --> 52:59.839
Ain't no way he's made up his mind yet.

53:00.810 --> 53:03.005
Wait, there he is, right there.

53:14.357 --> 53:16.484
Oh, what's the good word, coach?

53:19.296 --> 53:21.321
No? Shit.

53:23.533 --> 53:26.366
Truman Andrews. Here we come.

53:50.493 --> 53:52.393
Shit.

53:53.797 --> 53:55.458
Luann?

53:59.135 --> 54:00.363
Sir?

54:00.537 --> 54:03.199
Has the NCAA returned
any of my calls yet?

54:03.373 --> 54:04.772
No.

54:07.277 --> 54:10.246
Six, seven, eight, nine, 1 0,
1 1 at West Virginia.

54:10.413 --> 54:14.873
Kids that we wanted who are now
in West Virginia. Who's that?

54:15.485 --> 54:17.817
Bob Lambert. West Virginia.

54:17.988 --> 54:19.478
Shit.

54:19.656 --> 54:21.089
Twelve. West Virginia.

54:21.258 --> 54:24.421
Red, we gotta broaden our
recruiting base or something.

54:24.594 --> 54:27.927
We gotta get creative about...

54:28.198 --> 54:31.065
...who we're going after,
where we're going after them...

54:31.234 --> 54:34.431
...and how we're going after them.
lsn't that right, doc?

54:36.172 --> 54:37.969
Good morning, Red.

54:39.409 --> 54:42.139
Well, how are we doing?

54:42.312 --> 54:44.337
West Virginia will be
competitive next year.

54:44.514 --> 54:46.880
Yeah, very.
How about you?

54:47.751 --> 54:53.815
Well, Jack, l haven't heard anything
positive back yet.

54:53.990 --> 54:56.481
And l think l've done everything l can.

54:56.793 --> 55:00.126
Maybe we need more time.
l don't know.

55:01.097 --> 55:04.191
Time's the only thing
we don't have, Don.

55:04.367 --> 55:10.829
l mean, hell, it's already April.
Time is not our friend.

55:14.477 --> 55:16.945
Let me ask you a question.
Now, are you married?

55:17.113 --> 55:18.876
Yes, l am. 25 years in May.

55:19.049 --> 55:22.280
Twenty-five years. l am willing to bet...

55:23.320 --> 55:26.585
...that you didn't propose over the phone.

55:29.125 --> 55:30.956
No, l didn't.

55:31.127 --> 55:36.793
Okay. And l know damn well
that she didn't say yes in a letter.

55:39.736 --> 55:41.328
-Jack?
-Doc?

55:41.504 --> 55:44.940
-No, Jack. l know....
-Yes. Doc?

55:45.108 --> 55:46.336
You can do it.

55:48.478 --> 55:50.503
You're an outlaw. Pioneer.

55:51.014 --> 55:54.381
Gunslinger.
This is a whole new game, doc.

55:56.986 --> 55:58.977
You....

55:59.389 --> 56:01.016
You.

56:01.524 --> 56:05.085
There's a first time for everything, Don.

56:06.596 --> 56:09.258
lf we're gonna survive, this has
to be one of those times.

56:09.432 --> 56:11.900
And you're the only man that can do it.

56:22.846 --> 56:28.409
Excuse me, sir? Excuse me,
l'm sorry to bother you like this...

56:29.686 --> 56:33.417
...but my name is Don Dedmon,
l'm president of Marshall University.

56:33.990 --> 56:36.220
May l speak with you
for a moment, please?

56:37.327 --> 56:39.659
What are you doing in Kansas City, Don?

56:40.296 --> 56:44.665
My town, my school, we're hurting.

56:45.135 --> 56:50.129
We want to play football,
and we cannot do it without your help.

56:54.978 --> 56:56.536
Please.

57:16.433 --> 57:18.594
Guess who's going to change our diaper.

57:21.337 --> 57:24.431
Yeah!

57:24.607 --> 57:26.074
Get him!

57:26.242 --> 57:28.904
Need a little help here, Red.
He's heavier than you think.

57:29.078 --> 57:31.569
He's all wet.
He's all wet.

57:32.582 --> 57:34.072
Approved.

57:34.250 --> 57:38.243
''You will be allowed to play freshmen
at Marshall University.''

57:38.421 --> 57:41.117
-What's that right there? What's that?
-Here, put me down.

57:41.291 --> 57:44.590
That is signed by the president right there.
There he is. Stamped.

57:44.761 --> 57:47.286
Doc, we're gonna get us a football team.

57:48.364 --> 57:51.128
And that is why we are offering
your son something...

57:51.301 --> 57:53.701
...that no other school in the country can.

57:53.970 --> 57:58.839
lmmediate and substantial playing time
as a freshman.

58:14.157 --> 58:16.990
Time! l like the kid
who made the lay-up.

58:17.160 --> 58:20.618
This is the one l wanna talk to, right here.
What's your name, son?

58:25.235 --> 58:27.226
Ball, ball, ball!

58:32.008 --> 58:33.908
-That was a hell of a hit.
-Thank you.

58:34.077 --> 58:36.477
-Coach Dawson, from the football club.
-Bobby Jordan.

58:36.646 --> 58:38.910
-Ever play any football? None at all?
-No, sir.

58:39.082 --> 58:42.108
-No Pop Warner, no high school?
-No. Just baseball.

58:46.923 --> 58:48.857
Groovy. Come on, man.

58:49.259 --> 58:50.692
Hey, let me rap to you.

58:59.769 --> 59:01.327
Hey, how you doing?

59:03.973 --> 59:06.771
Hey. What's up, man?

59:20.623 --> 59:24.491
Strong finish.
That's a good-looking board.

59:25.795 --> 59:29.697
Good-looking board.
l'm tired of flying.

59:32.368 --> 59:37.305
Marshall Thundering Herd all-freshmen
team, led by quarterback John Cady...

59:38.975 --> 59:43.776
...handing the ball off
to the ever-talented Lucas Booth!

59:43.947 --> 59:46.677
He runs to the inside,
and who's on the outsider wing?

59:46.849 --> 59:49.647
Terry Gardner catches it,
pitches to Tennis Rice...

59:49.819 --> 59:53.311
...who's going downfield to
tight end Sam Boteck.

01:00:19.749 --> 01:00:20.977
l've never been.

01:00:21.150 --> 01:00:22.674
-Crazy. ln four years?
-Yeah.

01:00:22.852 --> 01:00:24.217
-The bonfire.
-l've never been.

01:00:24.387 --> 01:00:26.378
-Everyone's been to the bonfire.
-l haven't.

01:00:26.556 --> 01:00:28.888
-Do you eat marshmallows?
-l love marshmallows.

01:00:29.058 --> 01:00:32.824
-You've gotta come to the bonfire.
-Annie, order's up.

01:00:33.930 --> 01:00:36.160
-Ask her to come.
-l will, l will.

01:00:40.536 --> 01:00:42.470
-Here you go.
-Thanks.

01:00:43.539 --> 01:00:46.838
-Can we have some silverware?
-Sure.

01:00:52.482 --> 01:00:55.076
-Some guys have all the luck.
-Sorry?

01:00:55.251 --> 01:00:57.845
Your fiancé. He's a lucky guy.

01:00:59.922 --> 01:01:03.824
-Can you drive? Yeah.
-Yeah. We'll leave about 8?

01:01:12.468 --> 01:01:15.835
Keith? lt's your turn
to set the table!

01:01:16.005 --> 01:01:17.734
He's not here, Mom.

01:01:18.274 --> 01:01:20.572
-Where is he?
-l don't know.

01:01:22.412 --> 01:01:24.573
Okay, guys. First things first.

01:01:24.747 --> 01:01:26.977
Feel a connection to the guy next to you.

01:01:27.150 --> 01:01:30.119
Hand on a knee, hook an arm,
whatever it is.

01:01:30.520 --> 01:01:32.147
Come on, Herd.

01:01:32.321 --> 01:01:34.915
Look around, because these
are your teammates, young men.

01:01:35.091 --> 01:01:38.083
They're made up of three
returning varsity members.

01:01:38.261 --> 01:01:41.890
Randy Linden, George Olson, Nate Ruffin.

01:01:42.065 --> 01:01:46.058
Fifteen freshmen turning sophomores.

01:01:46.235 --> 01:01:48.829
And the rest of you, true freshmen...

01:01:49.005 --> 01:01:52.634
...very first time in college football
and walk-ons.

01:01:52.809 --> 01:01:55.175
Are you gonna play too, Tom?

01:01:56.379 --> 01:01:59.974
Remember, this is a game called football,
let's get to work. Let's go.

01:02:12.061 --> 01:02:14.461
We are going to be running
the Power l, gentlemen...

01:02:14.630 --> 01:02:16.723
...which obviously starts
with a quarterback.

01:02:16.899 --> 01:02:19.732
-Red, what are my choices?
-Dave Walsh.

01:02:19.902 --> 01:02:22.735
Solid athlete. Solid arm. Solid kid.

01:02:22.905 --> 01:02:24.372
Okay.

01:02:25.108 --> 01:02:26.632
Who else?

01:02:26.809 --> 01:02:31.405
-Jack, that's it.
-That's it, 1 0?

01:02:31.581 --> 01:02:32.809
That's it, coach.

01:02:32.982 --> 01:02:35.212
All right, guys.
Competition breeds improvement.

01:02:35.384 --> 01:02:39.081
Now, we need options here.
Let's look around, keep our eyes open.

01:02:39.255 --> 01:02:43.419
We need legs, hands and a decent arm.
Right there. Who's 86?

01:02:43.960 --> 01:02:47.259
That's Reggie Oliver.
Receiver from Alabama.

01:02:47.430 --> 01:02:50.228
Bear Bryant called me personally,
actually, to recommend him.

01:02:50.399 --> 01:02:53.664
-You wanna try him out at QB?
-Unless you think it's a bad idea.

01:02:54.036 --> 01:02:57.005
-Let's push them to the limit, men, huh?
-Right, coach.

01:03:03.579 --> 01:03:05.513
Come on, hit it, now!

01:03:07.116 --> 01:03:08.447
Check!

01:03:17.160 --> 01:03:18.286
Not good, coach.

01:03:33.309 --> 01:03:35.470
James, James. Get over here.

01:03:37.513 --> 01:03:39.174
That's supposed to be a post route.

01:03:39.348 --> 01:03:41.111
-Post?
-Post.

01:03:41.284 --> 01:03:44.310
You do know the difference between a
post route and a flag route?

01:03:44.487 --> 01:03:45.715
No, coach.

01:03:45.888 --> 01:03:49.346
All right, all right.
You see the big goalpost there?

01:03:49.525 --> 01:03:53.256
That's why they call it a post route. Post.
You head right to that post.

01:03:53.429 --> 01:03:55.124
Cut 1 0 yards, to the post.

01:03:55.298 --> 01:03:57.766
See the big pylon down
at the corner of the end zone?

01:03:57.934 --> 01:03:59.697
That's what we call a flag, all right?

01:03:59.869 --> 01:04:01.734
So when you're running the flag route...

01:04:01.904 --> 01:04:04.429
...1 0 yards to the corner of the end zone,
to the flag.

01:04:04.607 --> 01:04:06.438
-All right? All right.
-l got it.

01:04:06.609 --> 01:04:08.304
Do it again.

01:04:18.855 --> 01:04:21.255
Come on! Let's go!

01:04:21.791 --> 01:04:24.453
Nice speed, Booth! Nice speed!

01:04:26.128 --> 01:04:28.596
Nice speed. Shalhoop. Hey.

01:04:28.764 --> 01:04:31.824
-What are you doing?
-Oh, l kick the ball, coach.

01:04:32.001 --> 01:04:34.799
But after you kick it, son,
you're still a football player.

01:04:41.377 --> 01:04:44.039
Good job, George. Good job, George.
Come here, come here.

01:04:44.213 --> 01:04:46.078
-What's your name, 51 ?
-My name's Creole.

01:04:46.249 --> 01:04:48.274
Creole. This <i>Redbook</i>'s
taking me only so far.

01:04:48.451 --> 01:04:52.478
Urbanek, l need names. Last names on
everyone's helmet. All right? This afternoon.

01:04:52.655 --> 01:04:56.614
Now, Creole, the man outweighs you
by 75 pounds. Okay?

01:04:56.792 --> 01:04:58.384
When you're hitting him up high...

01:04:58.561 --> 01:05:01.587
...he'll beat you and you'll be
on your ass every time, all right?

01:05:01.764 --> 01:05:03.925
You gotta come in here,
you gotta get him low.

01:05:04.100 --> 01:05:07.558
Get him in the legs, okay? That's how
you'll keep him from coming through.

01:05:07.737 --> 01:05:10.535
-Stay low on him. Low, man.
-What should l do if he goes low?

01:05:10.706 --> 01:05:13.368
Good question. George says,
what does he do if he goes low?

01:05:13.542 --> 01:05:15.942
Five-one comes low.
Head slap and you're around him.

01:05:16.112 --> 01:05:18.774
Like that. You see that?
Head-slap the shit out of him.

01:05:29.759 --> 01:05:33.820
-Give me second team, McNally.
-We don't have a second team, Jack.

01:05:33.996 --> 01:05:37.762
Shit. Okay, yeah, we do
have a second team. Jackson! Urbanek!

01:05:37.934 --> 01:05:39.925
Lengyel, McNally, Dawson...

01:05:40.102 --> 01:05:42.263
...line up here.
Offensive line, watch this.

01:05:42.438 --> 01:05:45.635
-Coach, you don't have any pads on.
-Now, you just play ball, Olson.

01:05:47.777 --> 01:05:49.142
Quarterback's still standing.

01:05:49.312 --> 01:05:51.439
Big on big.
We can run an offense.

01:05:51.614 --> 01:05:55.846
We can save a young man's life.
Come on, now. Power l. Big on big.

01:06:01.257 --> 01:06:04.192
We got a huge problem
on the O-line, coach.

01:06:05.227 --> 01:06:08.162
l don't think it's because
the defensive line is so spectacular.

01:06:08.331 --> 01:06:09.662
No. No.

01:06:11.133 --> 01:06:15.797
Men. Power l. You know l'm a fan
of it, that's why l brought it here.

01:06:15.972 --> 01:06:18.805
l have learned in the last two weeks
that it is not working.

01:06:18.975 --> 01:06:22.570
So as of right now, the Power l
goes in the trash...

01:06:22.745 --> 01:06:27.079
...along with every flea-flicker,
double reverse...

01:06:27.249 --> 01:06:30.241
...and every other trick play
that you may have in your playbook.

01:06:30.419 --> 01:06:33.820
Get rid of it.
Men, it is time to simplify. Ball.

01:06:34.957 --> 01:06:37.323
So put our heads together here.

01:06:37.493 --> 01:06:39.654
What is the simplest offense...

01:06:41.731 --> 01:06:44.564
...that you have ever run
and actually won a football game?

01:06:44.734 --> 01:06:49.068
Any idea's a good idea. No right or wrong
in here today, men, let's talk it out.

01:06:49.238 --> 01:06:50.603
Well, there's always the Veer.

01:06:50.773 --> 01:06:54.641
The Veer. That's interesting.
Talk that out, Red.

01:06:55.244 --> 01:06:59.305
Well, the Veer's an option offense.
Spreads things out.

01:06:59.482 --> 01:07:01.074
Takes the focus off any one man.

01:07:01.250 --> 01:07:04.185
lt's designed for teams that don't
have a strong offensive line.

01:07:04.653 --> 01:07:08.111
Now, that is us in a nutshell.
Well, who runs it that we can talk to?

01:07:08.290 --> 01:07:10.690
Bill Yeoman came up with it
at Houston...

01:07:10.860 --> 01:07:14.193
...but other than West Virginia,
no one really runs it outside of Texas.

01:07:16.298 --> 01:07:18.823
-West Virginia runs the Veer?
-Yeah.

01:07:24.073 --> 01:07:28.442
Jack, that's crazy. We're rivals.

01:07:28.611 --> 01:07:31.705
You think they'll invite us to lunch
and hand over their playbook?

01:07:31.881 --> 01:07:33.781
They don't have to take us out to lunch.

01:07:33.949 --> 01:07:36.008
We'll pick some up on the way.

01:07:36.385 --> 01:07:40.685
Morgantown. The Veer. l like it.

01:07:45.027 --> 01:07:48.258
Eight-time Southern
Conference Champions, Red.

01:07:48.431 --> 01:07:52.697
Jack? Jack, l gotta tell you,
l really don't think this is your best idea.

01:07:53.035 --> 01:07:56.334
-Red! Good to see you again.
-Oh, coach.

01:07:56.505 --> 01:07:58.666
-How are you?
-How are you?

01:07:58.841 --> 01:08:00.900
-And this must be?
-Coach Jack Lengyel.

01:08:01.077 --> 01:08:03.477
Jack. Bobby Bowden.
Pleasure to meet you.

01:08:03.646 --> 01:08:05.273
lt's a pleasure to meet you.

01:08:05.448 --> 01:08:07.814
Bobby, thank you for taking
the time with us today.

01:08:07.983 --> 01:08:10.349
-My pleasure, not a problem.
-All right.

01:08:10.519 --> 01:08:12.077
Yes, sir.

01:08:12.588 --> 01:08:15.955
So l can't wait to hear.
What can l do for you boys?

01:08:17.660 --> 01:08:19.524
Well, the thing is...

01:08:20.563 --> 01:08:21.996
...coach...

01:08:22.564 --> 01:08:26.501
...we're thinking about adopting
the Veer this year.

01:08:26.734 --> 01:08:29.795
Now, l understand that to be
your bread and butter, as it were.

01:08:29.971 --> 01:08:32.667
We're just hoping that we could
come down here and maybe...

01:08:32.841 --> 01:08:34.810
...you could give us a few pointers.

01:08:41.850 --> 01:08:43.113
-Pointers?
-Tips.

01:08:43.285 --> 01:08:47.051
Advice. Anything that you'd
be willing to show us.

01:08:47.389 --> 01:08:52.587
Well, we'd really appreciate it. You seem
to be the man who runs it so well.

01:08:55.264 --> 01:08:56.595
He's good.

01:08:59.135 --> 01:09:01.626
-You're the best at the Veer.
-That's what they say!

01:09:01.804 --> 01:09:03.738
l'm coming straight to the man.

01:09:08.410 --> 01:09:10.344
Reg, l got your burger.

01:09:10.513 --> 01:09:13.243
-Chili on the fries?
-They were out.

01:09:13.415 --> 01:09:17.408
Come on, Stretch. Gonna be a rough year
if that's the best you can do.

01:09:28.229 --> 01:09:29.822
What?

01:10:10.000 --> 01:10:14.061
Playbooks. Research. Game film.

01:10:14.237 --> 01:10:17.035
Need anything copied or dubbed,
just see Kitty down the hall.

01:10:17.207 --> 01:10:19.698
Coach, you serious?

01:10:19.876 --> 01:10:23.471
Sure. We don't play y'all this year,
so, what the heck? Have at it.

01:10:23.647 --> 01:10:26.411
Just make sure you put everything back
where you found it.

01:10:26.583 --> 01:10:28.141
Deal.

01:10:28.918 --> 01:10:31.785
