<i>true freshmen in their lineup.</i>

01:15:54.377 --> 01:15:58.746
<i>And now, ladies and gentlemen, the</i>
<i>Morehead State Eagles are taking the field.</i>

01:16:04.354 --> 01:16:06.117
-How you feeling?
-Feeling good, coach.

01:16:06.289 --> 01:16:07.756
Feeling good.

01:16:11.794 --> 01:16:14.786
Go! Go! Go! Go!
Go! Go! Go!

01:16:39.756 --> 01:16:40.745
Oh, no.

01:16:48.965 --> 01:16:53.425
That's a clip! Where's the clip on that?
That's a clip, ref!

01:17:06.315 --> 01:17:08.306
lt's all right. lt's all right.

01:17:11.154 --> 01:17:13.520
They hit him low. All right?

01:17:14.924 --> 01:17:16.983
They hit him low. All right?

01:17:18.161 --> 01:17:20.925
l'm all right. l'm all right.

01:17:21.097 --> 01:17:23.088
<i>We hope he didn't re-injure his shoulder...</i>

01:17:23.266 --> 01:17:25.928
<i>...but I could hear the hit</i>
<i>from up here in the press box.</i>

01:17:26.102 --> 01:17:28.468
<i>Number 25, Nate Ruffin,</i>
<i>got blindsided and....</i>

01:17:31.407 --> 01:17:32.931
<i>--could not stop the return man.</i>

01:17:33.109 --> 01:17:36.806
<i>And now, with the extra point,</i>
<i>Morehead State is leading 29-6.</i>

01:17:36.979 --> 01:17:39.573
<i>The Marshall faithful</i>
<i>cannot be happy now.</i>

01:17:41.317 --> 01:17:43.945
Oliver! Oliver! Strong right!

01:17:45.655 --> 01:17:48.283
Switch! Switch!

01:17:49.192 --> 01:17:52.059
Forty! Set! Hike!

01:18:01.571 --> 01:18:02.799
Damn it.

01:18:04.874 --> 01:18:06.865
That's a shame.

01:18:11.080 --> 01:18:13.071
Gotta look him off.
lf you look him off....

01:18:13.249 --> 01:18:16.309
And you don't have to throw it.
You had 20 yards in front of you.

01:18:16.486 --> 01:18:18.044
Hut!

01:18:22.191 --> 01:18:24.591
-Ball! Ball!
-Get on the ball!

01:18:29.699 --> 01:18:31.860
That ain't a pitch,
you gotta get me the ball.

01:18:32.034 --> 01:18:34.867
-lf l make the pitch, catch the ball.
-You gotta get it to me.

01:18:35.037 --> 01:18:38.438
We gotta shake it up here.
We gotta start blitzing our linebacker.

01:18:55.324 --> 01:18:59.556
<i>That's a hard hit on number 29. Twenty-nine</i>
<i>is down and he's not getting up.</i>

01:18:59.729 --> 01:19:02.596
<i>I don't see number 29 on my roster here.</i>

01:19:02.765 --> 01:19:06.462
<i>There's just so many new faces on this</i>
<i>Marshall University Thundering Herd team.</i>

01:19:06.802 --> 01:19:09.032
Can you shake it off or not?

01:19:09.539 --> 01:19:12.030
Dawson! Dawson!

01:19:14.944 --> 01:19:17.276
What do you think?
We gotta get three points.

01:19:17.446 --> 01:19:20.108
We don't get any points on the board,
we'll lose them.

01:19:20.283 --> 01:19:23.081
All right, we need our three.
lt's gonna help out the morale.

01:19:23.252 --> 01:19:26.710
Send the kicking team in. Let's go.
Gotta end this game with three points.

01:19:26.889 --> 01:19:29.449
Yeah. Send them in.
Kicking team, let's go.

01:19:42.939 --> 01:19:45.237
Dawson. Send them in!

01:19:48.311 --> 01:19:50.074
Call it in, Red!

01:19:51.547 --> 01:19:53.208
Call it in!

01:19:56.953 --> 01:19:58.750
Send them in!

01:20:00.957 --> 01:20:02.390
Kick it! Kick it!

01:20:03.192 --> 01:20:05.251
Field-goal unit! Let's go!

01:20:14.103 --> 01:20:15.593
Let's go!

01:20:35.925 --> 01:20:39.520
<i>These kids do have plenty of heart,</i>
<i>but just not enough skill or experience...</i>

01:20:39.695 --> 01:20:42.163
<i>...to compete at this level.</i>
<i>And with this loss...</i>

01:20:42.331 --> 01:20:46.028
<i>...next week's first home game against</i>
<i>Xavier University won't be any easier.</i>

01:20:46.202 --> 01:20:49.831
<i>The Xavier game will be the first</i>
<i>home game since the devastating crash...</i>

01:20:50.006 --> 01:20:52.941
<i>...that killed 75 players and fans.</i>

01:20:53.109 --> 01:20:56.943
<i>After this painful loss,</i>
<i>the Marshall faithful must be wondering...</i>

01:20:57.113 --> 01:20:59.411
<i>...if they've done the right thing.</i>

01:21:17.700 --> 01:21:19.327
Pick it up.

01:21:20.102 --> 01:21:21.660
Pick what up?
Pick my jersey up?

01:21:21.837 --> 01:21:24.670
lt ain't your jersey, it's Joe Hood's jersey.
Now, pick it up.

01:21:24.840 --> 01:21:26.569
-Who's Joe Hood?
-You don't know him.

01:21:26.742 --> 01:21:29.336
l'm not gonna ask you again.
Now, pick it up!

01:21:30.646 --> 01:21:36.778
Look, man, l came here to play ball, and l'm
gonna be as respectful as l can be...

01:21:36.952 --> 01:21:40.945
...but l'm the one playing
for this team now. l'm number 33.

01:21:41.123 --> 01:21:44.024
That's my jersey.
l'll do whatever l want with it!

01:21:46.595 --> 01:21:49.496
Hey, break it up! Break it up!
Listen to me, break it up right--

01:21:54.501 --> 01:22:00.201
Well, Meckstroth's ankle's just a sprain,
so he should be better by Saturday.

01:22:00.373 --> 01:22:03.240
And Meadows' hamstring, it's okay too.

01:22:03.410 --> 01:22:06.538
What about Ruffin's shoulder?
What'd the doc say?

01:22:06.980 --> 01:22:11.144
Well, it ain't good.
l think we better sit him, Jack.

01:22:12.252 --> 01:22:13.981
Well, he's not gonna like that.

01:22:14.154 --> 01:22:17.487
Well, he ain't gonna like trying
to write with the other hand, either...

01:22:17.657 --> 01:22:20.057
...and that's what he's looking at
if he keeps going.

01:22:20.226 --> 01:22:23.889
Okay, well, let's see what he can do
in practice. Thank you.

01:22:25.098 --> 01:22:28.534
Split right, 434-Z-Slant.
Let it develop and trust it.

01:22:28.701 --> 01:22:30.168
Trust it. Make the play. Go.

01:22:30.336 --> 01:22:31.598
Here he comes, D!

01:22:36.309 --> 01:22:38.277
Forty-two! Set, hut!

01:22:48.988 --> 01:22:51.115
What's your problem?
We're on the same team!

01:22:57.330 --> 01:22:59.457
Make them commit.
Make it so. Make it so.

01:23:05.738 --> 01:23:06.762
Set, hut!

01:23:15.315 --> 01:23:17.442
Hey! Break it up! Break it up now!

01:23:20.220 --> 01:23:22.711
l can't take that!
Man, you want some of me?

01:23:22.889 --> 01:23:24.652
Get back there!

01:23:28.361 --> 01:23:30.124
Get back in the huddle!

01:23:38.905 --> 01:23:41.135
All right, let's go.

01:23:46.079 --> 01:23:48.946
Fourteen! Set, hut!

01:23:54.721 --> 01:23:57.383
That's it. Walsh, did you see that?
That's success!

01:24:03.897 --> 01:24:05.524
Ruffin!

01:24:06.166 --> 01:24:09.294
Ruffin! What the hell
is the matter with you?

01:24:09.469 --> 01:24:11.699
Just playing till the whistle blew, coach.

01:24:11.871 --> 01:24:13.168
Bullshit!

01:24:13.873 --> 01:24:16.774
You think you're the only one
who has a right to be pissed off?

01:24:16.943 --> 01:24:19.377
You think you're the only one
that's had it rough?

01:24:53.079 --> 01:24:56.947
Ruffin, get up. Get up, Ruffin.
That's enough.

01:24:57.116 --> 01:24:58.777
Go water down.

01:24:59.852 --> 01:25:01.877
-Oliver, you okay?
-Yeah.

01:25:04.724 --> 01:25:06.555
Where are you going?

01:25:08.995 --> 01:25:10.963
What the hell are we
doing out there, Jack?

01:25:11.130 --> 01:25:14.190
We're trying to run a Veer.
We're trying to get ready for Xavier.

01:25:14.367 --> 01:25:15.698
Really?

01:25:17.337 --> 01:25:20.067
Feels a lot more
like Bloody Knuckles to me.

01:25:20.240 --> 01:25:23.732
l mean, it feels like we're just
punching walls out there, Jack.

01:25:24.744 --> 01:25:27.235
l mean, we're not actually helping them.

01:25:27.413 --> 01:25:31.042
We're bringing the worst out in them.
Shit, we're bringing the worst out in me.

01:25:32.452 --> 01:25:33.885
And for what?

01:25:34.053 --> 01:25:38.456
So that we can collect pity applause
in front of every college in the conference?

01:25:42.161 --> 01:25:44.356
You didn't know Rick Tolley.

01:25:44.864 --> 01:25:46.092
l did.

01:25:46.566 --> 01:25:50.058
And on the day that he died, he said...

01:25:50.236 --> 01:25:54.900
...the only thing that they judge us on,
the only thing that counts, is winning.

01:25:55.074 --> 01:25:56.632
Nothing else matters.

01:25:57.210 --> 01:26:00.646
So, what do we do?
How are we honoring their memory?

01:26:00.813 --> 01:26:05.546
We put together a team
that doesn't win. Can't win.

01:26:05.718 --> 01:26:11.281
Not this week, not this season.
Hell, maybe not ever.

01:26:12.892 --> 01:26:15.656
We're not honoring them, Jack.

01:26:17.930 --> 01:26:19.830
We're disgracing them.

01:26:25.004 --> 01:26:26.562
l'm done.

01:26:38.418 --> 01:26:40.648
Don't bench me, coach.

01:26:44.624 --> 01:26:47.184
-Jesus, Nate, have you even slept?
-Not now.

01:26:48.628 --> 01:26:51.188
Not before our first home game.

01:26:51.364 --> 01:26:54.891
Now, look, Nate, your shoulder
is in bad shape.

01:26:55.068 --> 01:26:56.899
The rest is gonna do it some good.

01:26:57.070 --> 01:27:00.597
No. No, it ain't.
The rest ain't gonna do it good.

01:27:00.773 --> 01:27:04.300
Nate, l'm not questioning your courage
or your drive, okay?

01:27:04.477 --> 01:27:07.640
-My shoulder's fine.
-This shoulder?

01:27:07.814 --> 01:27:10.078
lt's ready to take the field?
lt's ready for hits?

01:27:10.249 --> 01:27:11.682
-My shoulder's fine.
-Yes or no?

01:27:11.851 --> 01:27:13.648
-My shoulder's fine. Yeah.
-This one?

01:27:13.820 --> 01:27:16.050
-Can it take hits like that?
-My shoulder's fine.

01:27:16.222 --> 01:27:17.746
Gonna be a lot harder than that.

01:27:17.924 --> 01:27:20.449
My shoulder's fine.

01:27:30.203 --> 01:27:31.966
Talk to me.

01:27:32.138 --> 01:27:34.299
Oh, coach.

01:27:38.311 --> 01:27:41.644
That was my team.

01:27:46.819 --> 01:27:49.947
They left it in my hands.

01:27:53.760 --> 01:27:57.594
Oh, Nate.
No, no, no, they did not.

01:27:57.764 --> 01:27:59.493
No.

01:27:59.665 --> 01:28:01.724
They just left.

01:28:03.035 --> 01:28:05.026
Then why?

01:28:09.342 --> 01:28:11.435
Why, coach?

01:28:13.613 --> 01:28:15.308
Why?

01:28:18.885 --> 01:28:20.113
l don't know.

01:28:55.021 --> 01:28:57.990
The board voted you out this morning.

01:28:58.157 --> 01:29:01.388
What? May l ask why?

01:29:01.561 --> 01:29:06.828
Come on, Don.
You were always a temporary solution.

01:29:06.999 --> 01:29:09.490
You said it yourself after Roland resigned.

01:29:09.669 --> 01:29:12.502
You were just a Band-Aid, remember?

01:29:13.139 --> 01:29:16.199
ls this about the football program, Paul?

01:29:17.810 --> 01:29:20.278
The crash just cut too damn deep, Don.

01:29:20.446 --> 01:29:24.246
lt's not just the team that's bleeding.
lt's not just the school.

01:29:24.417 --> 01:29:25.850
lt's the entire town.

01:29:26.018 --> 01:29:28.578
Do you have any idea
what it's like for Annie right now?

01:29:28.754 --> 01:29:31.689
She can't read the paper.
She can't watch the news.

01:29:31.858 --> 01:29:35.589
She can't even go to work
without being reminded of football...

01:29:35.761 --> 01:29:40.664
...which reminds her of the crash,
which reminds her of my dead son!

01:29:43.870 --> 01:29:45.633
Paul.

01:29:45.805 --> 01:29:48.273
This isn't about football, is it?

01:29:48.975 --> 01:29:53.912
And this isn't about Annie.
And this isn't about the town, Paul.

01:29:54.080 --> 01:29:58.642
This is about the loss of your son.
And l'm sorry.

01:29:58.818 --> 01:30:02.618
But until you find the strength
to deal with that pain...

01:30:02.788 --> 01:30:05.780
...nothing's going to get any better.

01:30:05.958 --> 01:30:09.724
No matter how many presidents
you fire, Paul.

01:30:30.082 --> 01:30:32.642
Just about closed. Sorry.

01:30:34.520 --> 01:30:39.287
My wife tells me you've got
the best apple pie in Huntington.

01:30:40.560 --> 01:30:42.551
Depends on the apple.

01:30:43.963 --> 01:30:46.397
Well, do you mind if l try?

01:30:48.267 --> 01:30:49.962
Hey, Annie.

01:30:58.077 --> 01:31:00.637
-Annie Cantrell?
-Yeah.

01:31:02.114 --> 01:31:04.981
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

01:31:14.694 --> 01:31:16.525
Mr. Griffen?

01:31:17.463 --> 01:31:20.557
l don't believe we've been
formally introduced yet.

01:31:20.733 --> 01:31:22.633
l'm Jack Lengyel.

01:31:25.471 --> 01:31:27.029
Thank you.

01:31:33.546 --> 01:31:37.038
l understand Don Dedmon
lost his job this week.

01:31:37.216 --> 01:31:40.708
He's well-qualified, he'll find a place.

01:31:44.690 --> 01:31:48.922
You know, if you have a problem
with anything that happens on the field...

01:31:49.095 --> 01:31:52.121
...blame me, not him. l'm the coach here.

01:31:52.298 --> 01:31:55.665
And what happens out there
is my responsibility, not his.

01:31:55.835 --> 01:31:58.360
You're not from here,
you weren't here last November...

01:31:58.537 --> 01:32:01.301
...so l don't expect you
to understand this.

01:32:02.842 --> 01:32:04.935
This is not about what happened
on that field.

01:32:05.111 --> 01:32:07.944
This is about what happened
to this town.

01:32:08.114 --> 01:32:09.877
This is not a game.

01:32:28.467 --> 01:32:32.460
l'm real sorry about your son,
Mr. Griffen.

01:32:34.240 --> 01:32:36.936
He was a hell of a running back.
l bet you were real proud.

01:32:37.109 --> 01:32:39.339
Please don't talk about him
like you knew him.

01:32:41.714 --> 01:32:43.909
l was proud of him,
and l'm still proud of him.

01:34:36.896 --> 01:34:38.329
He was right, you know.

01:34:42.034 --> 01:34:45.492
-Who was right?
-Your boy Tolley.

01:34:46.272 --> 01:34:49.867
Winning is everything
and nothing else matters.

01:34:50.042 --> 01:34:53.705
l mean, l've said that
so many times myself...

01:34:53.879 --> 01:34:57.406
...l've lost count. You know?

01:34:57.583 --> 01:35:00.984
And it doesn't matter in what sport,
and it doesn't matter what country...

01:35:01.153 --> 01:35:06.113
...any coach who's worth a darn
in this business believes those words.

01:35:06.292 --> 01:35:08.055
Fact.

01:35:11.964 --> 01:35:13.955
And then l came here.

01:35:16.302 --> 01:35:17.769
For the first time in my life...

01:35:17.937 --> 01:35:21.600
...hell, maybe for the first time
in the history of sports...

01:35:21.774 --> 01:35:25.107
...suddenly, it's just not true anymore.

01:35:26.445 --> 01:35:29.539
At least not here, not now. No.

